-- Export-Import Bank of China Has $11 Billion of Shipping Loans
-- B y   M i c h e l l e   W i e s e   B o c k m a n n
-- 2012-05-15T15:17:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-15/export-import-bank-of-china-has-11-billion-of-shipping-loans.html
Export-Import Bank of China  has an
$11 billion shipping-loan portfolio and ranks 15th among lenders
to the global industry, the head of its shipping-finance
division said.  The bank has 100 shipowner clients, including foreigners,
said Gao Zefeng, director of its Shipping Finance Division II,
Transport-Finance Department. He spoke today at a conference in
 London .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Michelle Wiese Bockmann in London at 
 mwiesebockma@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
